{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Austreskorve Glacier | other_name = | photo = Antarctica, Norway territorial claim (Queen Maud Land, 2015).svg | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Location of Queen Maud Land in Antarctica | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Austreskorve Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Queen Maud Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|71|50|S|5|40|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Austreskorve Glacier''' ({{coord|71|50|S|5|40|E|type:glacier_region:AQ_source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a broad [[glacier]] in the [[Mühlig-Hofmann Mountains]] which drains north from a position just east of the head of [[Vestreskorve Glacier]] and passes along the east side of [[Breplogen Mountain]]. It was mapped and named from surveys and from air photos by the [[Sixth Norwegian Antarctic Expedition]] (1956&ndash;60).
