'''bEnd.3''' is a mouse brain [[cell line]] derived from [[BALB/c]] mice. The cell line is commonly used in vascular research and studies of [[endothelium|endothelial]] brain tissue.<ref>{{cite journal|pmc=4636729|title=Novel characterization of bEnd.3 cells that express lymphatic vessel endothelial hyaluronan receptor|date=4 June 2014|journal=Lymphology|volume=47|issue=2|pages=73–81|first1=D|last1=Yuen|display-authors=etal}}</ref> In particular, bEnd.3 cells can serve as [[blood-brain barrier]] models for [[ischemia]].<ref>{{cite journal|title=Characterisation of a mouse cerebral microvascular endothelial cell line (bEnd.3) after oxygen glucose deprivation and reoxygenation|first1=Kai|last1=Chin|display-authors=etal|journal=Clinical and Experimental Pharmacology and Physiology|date=29 April 2016|doi=10.1111/1440-1681.12587|volume=43|pages=777–786}}</ref>
