[[Image:Mercure carte antoniadi.jpg|thumb|1934 map showing the Pieria albedo feature]]

The '''Derain''' [[quadrangle (geography)|quadrangle]] (H-10) is one of [[List of quadrangles on Mercury|fifteen quadrangles on Mercury]]. It runs from 288 to 360° longitude and from -25 to 25° latitude. Named after the [[Derain (crater)|Derain]] crater, it was mapped in detail for the first time after ''[[MESSENGER]]'' entered orbit around [[Mercury (planet)|Mercury]] in 2011. It had not been mapped prior to that point because it was one of the six quadrangles that was not illuminated when ''[[Mariner 10]]'' made its flybys in 1974 and 1975. These six quadrangles continued to be known by their [[list of albedo features on Mercury|albedo feature]] names, with this one known as the Pieria quadrangle.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Page/mercuryQuadMap| title=1:5 Million-Scale Maps of Mercury| publisher=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature (USGS/IAU/NASA)| accessdate=2013-09-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://history.nasa.gov/SP-423/p21.htm| title=SP-423 Atlas of Mercury| page=21| publisher=NASA| accessdate=2013-09-19}}</ref>

The massive [[Skinakas Basin]] overlaps the border of this quadrangle and neighboring [[Eminescu quadrangle]].

